<br>
Now I am not really sure why you included the section about sex.  Aside from an absolute conviction that any religion that prohibits sex among its practicioners will die a very quick cultural death, I don't see it's pertinence.  I find it amusing that god has to give us sex or he can't beat satan, or that his minion does it as an aside and not under directive from god.  It also amuses me that by this verse, Heather needs her husband's permission to have a headache.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
