<br>
The higher law, (turning your cheek -forgiveness--instead of eye for an eye.)  Loving your neighbor and God as Brit said pretty much covered the spirit of the laws and the became the new convenant.<br>
<br>
So some would ask why do we even have the OT then.  The reason is that it serves as a testimony of the divinity of Jesus Christ.  It contains the prophesies of His coming.   It also contains many wonderful stories of faith that can teach us how to love God and follow Him. And stories of failure that show us how to avoid sin. <br>
<br>
The reason that Peter received the vision is that there was a misunderstanding among members of the church that the Mosiac law should still be practiced.  They didnt get it, so God had to reveal himself to his prophet Peter to keep error from entering into the church.  (Thanks Dave for making my point for me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
