<br>
Then again, it could just be one man with a political agenda advancing his personal glory on this earth.  He can't convert you because you don't want to give up your meal plan.  He can't convert you because you don't want to mutilate your genitalia.  He can't convert you because there is so much in conflict between the culture and the theology that it will never fly.  We have already seen the church re-write itself to better assimilate other cultures (hello?  easter?  Dec 25? flood myths?  anyone?) Hence a 'vision' that removes all the road blocks and allows him to discriminatorily preach whatever he can sell and abolish whatever he can't.  Good thing he had that vision 3 times, or we might not have taken him seriously.<br>
<br>
Laws are not given as symbols.  Laws are given to obey.  A wedding ring is given as a symbol.  A parchment degree is given as a symbol.  A traffic signal is given to obey, with direct and measurable consequences if it is not.  To Heather's credit, she is trying very hard to obey as many laws as she can distinguish.  Her personal integrity demands it and she does not hide herself behind flattery and eloquence.  She will flat out declare whom she thinks is going to hell and why. She has some trouble with conflicting laws and apparently avoids the cognitive dissonance by refusing to study that area of law, keeping her eyes closed to it.  Yet others blithely dismiss and walk away from the same area if they but glimpse it.  You have the decalogue reduced to two general platitudes!  Your logic about J-Zeus coming not to destroy the laws but to fulfill them breaks down as soon as YOU ABOLISH THE LAWS! At that point he HAS come to destroy the law! Your &quot;In other words&quot; quip is like saying &quot;Thou Shalt Not Kill...in other words killing that guy is okay&quot; and equates directly to self-contradiction and hypocrisy.  God authored the law.  To cite 'higher' law means that there is an authority higher than god.<br>
<br>
If by making your point for you, you are meaning I exposed the hypocrisy of it, you are very welcome.  If by making your point for you, you mean something I said in some way validates your theistic position, I think you need to reread my post.  The bible as work supports only men and their political agendas; or, if you are correct about god, then it supports only satan.  Either way, it is a horrible thing to follow.<br>
